---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service — Still Us" description="The terms governing your use of the Still Us mobile application.">
  <Navbar />
  <main class="pt-24 pb-0">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="bg-canvas-darker py-16 px-6" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #15152A 0%, #26263B 100%);">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-label uppercase text-accent mb-3">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="font-display text-4xl text-white mb-4 tracking-[-0.02em]">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="text-white/45 text-sm">Last updated: January 1, 2026</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="bg-canvas py-16 px-6">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto prose-legal">

        <section>
          <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p>
            By downloading, installing, or using Still Us ("the App"), you agree to be bound
            by these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree, do not use the App.
            These Terms form a binding agreement between you and Still Us.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>2. Eligibility</h2>
          <p>
            You must be at least 13 years of age to use Still Us. By using the App, you
            represent and warrant that you meet this requirement. If you are between 13 and
            18 years of age, you represent that your parent or guardian has reviewed and
            agrees to these Terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>3. Your Account</h2>
          <p>
            You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials.
            You agree to notify us immediately of any unauthorised use of your account. We are
            not liable for any loss resulting from someone else using your account with or without
            your knowledge.
          </p>
          <p>
            You may not create accounts for others without permission, or use the App to
            impersonate another person.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>4. Partner Linking</h2>
          <p>
            Still Us is designed for use by two people in a relationship ("partners"). By
            linking with a partner using an invite code, you consent to sharing certain data
            with that person as described in our Privacy Policy.
          </p>
          <p>
            You are responsible for ensuring you only share your invite code with someone you
            trust and intend to connect with. We are not responsible for any consequences
            arising from sharing your invite code with the wrong person.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>5. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p>You agree not to use the App to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Harass, threaten, or harm another person</li>
            <li>Share illegal, abusive, or otherwise harmful content</li>
            <li>Attempt to gain unauthorised access to any part of the App or its infrastructure</li>
            <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble the App</li>
            <li>Use the App for any commercial purpose without our express written consent</li>
            <li>Violate any applicable law or regulation</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to terminate your account and access to the App immediately
            if we determine, in our sole discretion, that you have violated these terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>6. Content You Create</h2>
          <p>
            You retain ownership of the content you create in Still Us (messages, tasks,
            events, etc.). By creating content, you grant Still Us a limited, non-exclusive
            licence to store and process that content solely for the purpose of providing
            the service to you and your linked partner.
          </p>
          <p>
            You are solely responsible for the content you create. We do not review user
            content and are not liable for any content you or your partner create.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>7. Special Messages</h2>
          <p>
            Still Us provides special message types including time-delayed, time-locked, and
            password-locked messages. These features are provided as-is. While we make
            reasonable efforts to deliver time-delayed messages at the specified time,
            delivery may be affected by device settings, push notification permissions,
            or infrastructure issues. We are not liable for late or undelivered messages.
          </p>
          <p>
            Password-locked messages are verified server-side. You are responsible for
            communicating the password to your partner through a separate channel.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>8. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>
            The Still Us App, including its design, code, graphics, and branding, is owned
            by Still Us and protected by applicable intellectual property laws. You may not
            copy, modify, distribute, or create derivative works based on the App without
            our express written permission.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>9. Disclaimers</h2>
          <p>
            THE APP IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED,
            INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A
            PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT. WE DO NOT WARRANT THAT THE APP WILL
            BE UNINTERRUPTED, ERROR-FREE, OR SECURE.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, STILL US SHALL NOT BE
            LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES,
            INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO LOSS OF DATA, LOSS OF PROFITS, OR DAMAGE TO
            RELATIONSHIPS, ARISING FROM YOUR USE OF OR INABILITY TO USE THE APP.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>11. Termination</h2>
          <p>
            You may stop using Still Us at any time by deleting the App from your device.
            You may request deletion of your account and data by contacting us at
            <a href="mailto:support@stillus.app">support@stillus.app</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to suspend or terminate your access to the App at any time,
            for any reason, including violation of these Terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>12. Changes to These Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these Terms from time to time. We will notify you of material
            changes via in-app notification. Your continued use of the App following
            notification of changes constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>13. Governing Law</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms are governed by the laws of the jurisdiction in which Still Us
            operates, without regard to conflict of law principles.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>14. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            For questions about these Terms, contact us at:<br />
            <a href="mailto:support@stillus.app">support@stillus.app</a>
          </p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose-legal section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .prose-legal h2 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1A1A2E;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .prose-legal p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #6B7280;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
  }

  .prose-legal ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  .prose-legal li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #6B7280;
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .prose-legal li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.6em;
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #8B7FD4;
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  .prose-legal a {
    color: #8B7FD4;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .prose-legal a:hover {
    color: #6355B0;
  }

  .prose-legal strong {
    color: #1A1A2E;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
